      "content": "Choosing to switch medications on your own without professional guidance can be harmful. Though some people report using St. John's Wort as a substitute, the switch between SSRIs and St. John's Wort isn't as simple as alternating doses, as they affect the body differently. Additionally, there isn't a standardized dose of St. John's Wort equivalent to a 50 mg dose of Sertraline—effects vary widely. You must consult your doctor to explore alternative treatments safely. Immediately reaching out again to them, or considering a pharmacy service that can work with your healthcare provider, might help expedite your needs.",
